# PLAN-DELEGATE COMMAND — DISABLED (2026-05-08)

This command has been disabled as part of the AI architecture rebuild.
The plan-delegate pattern (official Claude plans → delegates to DeepSeek) is replaced.

New workflow: DeepSeek is the default master. Official Claude is only called on-demand
for architecture review of sensitive areas (auth, payments, DB migrations, large diffs).

- DeepSeek master entry: `scripts/ai/cc_deepseek_master.sh`
- On-demand Claude review: `scripts/ai/ask_official_claude_review.sh tasks/ai/xxx.md logs/ai/xxx.diff.patch`

Original backup: `scripts/ai_backup_20260508_144425/.claude_commands/plan-delegate.md`
